The man convicted of shooting and killing Vaal student Jabulile Nhlapo last year has been sentenced to life imprisonment. Lebogang Mofokeng was found guilty on Monday of premeditated murder in the High Court in Johannesburg sitting at the Palm Ridge Magistrate’s Court on Gauteng’s East Rand. Twenty three-year-old Nhlapo who was Mofokeng’s ex-girlfriend was fatally shot at a student commune in Vanderbijlpark in May 2018.   WATCH RELATED VIDEO BELOW: 